-- Explosion Damages Commuter Train in Southern Russia, RIA Novosti Reports
-- Brad Cook
-- 2010-09-20T05:12:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/explosion-damages-commuter-train-in-southern-russia-ria-novosti-reports.html

          
          
             A bomb damaged a commuter train in
southern Russia, RIA Novosti reported, citing local officials.  
 A homemade bomb containing about 200 grams of TNT exploded
on the tracks as the train passed, the Moscow-based newspaper
said. The train wasn’t carrying passengers and wasn’t derailed,
RIA said.  
          
          


  


        